rComments: She is a nice professor. If you read all powerpoint, you will get a great grade, because the exam is come from the her Lecture.
She is the best prof, so sweet and gives great lectures.

What a wonderful professor! Not only is she a great professor, but she is also a really nice and caring person. I am enjoying this class so much! Every lecture is fun and interesting. As long as you put the work in, you will enjoy the class and do well!

A truly incredible example of what I wish all Profs were like. She takes an already interesting topic and makes it better with every lecture. I had worried that 2.5 hour lectures would drag... they didn't. She made time to meet with me individually, writes very fair exams and is genuinely just a lovely person. I highly recommend taking this class!

Wonderful and amazing prof! She is super caring about her students, and her lectures are simply beautiful. She is organized and she conveys lots of new info in very interesting ways. You won't get bored in her class at all! She makes learning very easy and fun. 15/10 prof, would recommend her to anyone.

Wonderful professor! Not only was she caring towards her students but she also clearly has a passion for what she does and it shows through her teaching style. I enjoyed the pacing of this course and I would recommend it as a fun elective to anyone who has an interest in music!

The lectures can get boring, but she is a very warm person and I found myself letting go of a lot of anxiety every time I logged into her classroom. The weekly homework is very easy and never takes more than a half hour to finish. It is pleasant course because so much of it is listening to beautiful music! Make a lot of notes and flashcards.

Took this class because of elective requirements for my program, and ended up loving every second of it. It's unfortunate that professors that care about their students as much as her are an exception rather than the rule.
Theres a reason everyone loves her. As someone who knows nil about music even I found her class very enjoyable. A teacher who makes u fall in love w the subject? Does it get any better

Dr. Bazinet is a very empathetic prof. Her course is indeed an easy 9.0-10.0. Midterms have no surprises and are completely fair and pretty easy. She even puts a bonus questions in the midterms to help boost your mark. She was super caring when I emailed her for help and even corrected my assignment before it was due. I wish every prof was like her

A shining example of what professors should adhere to. Clearly very passionate about the subject material. I often find that university classes can ruin what is otherwise an interesting topic, but this course was something special. 11/10 would recommend taking this. Read the lecture slides in advance, listen to the lectures and you're golden.
Great Prof! Love the class, great class for movie lovers. Not super hard, but need to do your fair share of work and movie watching.

I really loved Bazinet. She's so nice and polite. She made lectures interesting despite them being online, and she was accessible outside of class. The assignments, quizzes and final were also very fair. I worked hard in this class and ended with an A+. I would definitely recommend it as a summer elective.

I would absolutely recommend this prof and this class. I took it online in the summer semester and had a great experience. Very fair quizzes/final exam and easy assignments. I did not read the textbook and had no problems. All the information can easily be found on the slides so attendance isn't mandatory, but i always enjoyed her lectures.

easy class, study the slides and you'll be fine. Pay attention to the movie clips played in class as you'll have to recognize them for the midterm. you have a midterm, a paper and a final exam. The midterm was really easy (just review the slides) and I wrote my paper in 4hrs and was in the As. Idk about the final ( COVID  optional).

Professor Bazinet is so knowledgeable and nice and has such a soothing voice, made the semester enjoyable and fly by. Her knowledge of music and movies is remarkable, and you finish the course feeling that you really learned something new. Very fair evaluations. Although the class was online, it was very well built and worth going to every lecture.

Just finished the class with her and it was amazing! She is so sweet and caring and you can tell that she really wants her students to do well in the class. She is also very accessible outside of class time and responds to emails in a very timely manner and in great detail. Highly recommend her as a prof!

L'une des meilleures professeures de l'U d'O. Elle est très accessible à l'extérieur des classe, toujours attentive et patiente pour répondre à nos questions. Ces travaux sont intéressants à faire, tout comme l'est le cours. J'ai adoré ce dernier, et l'ai recommandé à tous mes amis. Je suis ravie d'avoir pu étudier avec elle.

A brilliant Prof who truly cares about her students. She wants you to absorb as much as possible but facilitates and provides ways for you to learn. I knew nothing about music, by the end of the two courses I took with her I became a music connoisseur (lol). She was very accommodating during office hours and e-mails. One of the best profs ever..

Her Music in the Movies class is not attendance mandatory but I'd highly recommend it as the midterm and final contain direct references to clips shown in class. Overall a wonderful prof! Extremely accommodating and available before and after classes. Would definitely recommend her as a professor.

Her class was a rather easy one, given that I had some music knowledge. Her tests and assignments are very straightforward and she provided all the notes for the course, so you just have to follow what she says in class to absorb the information. Would definitely recommend her as a prof!

Very sweet professor and fun material. Go to class and you'll do well for sure (as long as you study)! The lecture can be very boring, but her exams are very straight-forward. Would recommend as an elective!

I absolutely love Professor Bazinet. She is a model for how all profs should teach. She pretty much reads off slides and posts them on bright space, so attendance isn't necessary. She gives you a literal list word for word of what will be on the midterm/exam. You need to work for it, but I showed up to two lectures and finished with an A+.

She is such a great prof! Her lectures are super helpful and she has all the info on the slides (this is helpful but doesn't mean that going to class is useless). Her lectures are interesting and treat a subject that everyone can easily understand and learn. Honestly one of my favorite classes

Very caring, delightful, and cool prof. :) Got an A+ in the Music in the Movies course. Had to work really hard for it despite having ten years of music experience. Loved her lectures. Sometimes seen her outside of class coincidentally. Always a pleasure to talk to. Introduced a love of Lord of the Rings to me. :) One of my favorite movies now.

a role model professor to all other proffs here at uottawa. unparalleled kindness and compassion. always eager and accessible to help. any problems? explain and she'll understand within reason. the course itself is straight forward, just know key terms and composers . some lectures may seem dry, but attendance isn't mandatory. 100% recommend!

Incredible professor! She has such a kind heart and caring nature. Her passion for music only matches her desire for her students to succeed. She prepares many reviews and examples that translate perfectly in her exams. She really opens your eyes to a new function of music used in movies! A music background is not necessary but incredibly helpful.

Mme Bazinet is the quintessential mom-prof: she really has all of her students' best interests at heart. Though I didn't find her lectures that compelling, she no doubt has profound knowledge of the material (although she does read off power-points, so skipping lectures won't hurt too much). Assignments are easy, but make sure to study for finals.
Excellent professor!! Very fair in exams and prepares students well for finals. Content of lectures reflects exams!
Honestly the sweetest person I've ever met. Is always happy to see you outside of class, super caring and understanding. Would take any class with her because of how amazing she is.

She's a very nice and caring prof who clearly loves music in movies. The class could get a little boring from time to time, but overall was good. A midterm, assignment and exam. Easy enough if you pay attention or know about music. LEARN THE COMPOSERS. Not a difficult class to pass or even get an A in.

Dr. Bazinet is an amazing and caring professor. She always looking for ways to convey subject matter more effectively to her students. Fair grading. She is encouraging and makes time for all of her students. If you have a problem go see her!

AMAZING Professor. I adored every second with her. I took history 2 and 4 with her for my BMus as well as my seminar and I could not be happier. She is so kind and makes sure that if you put in the effort, you get the marks. She taught exactly what you needed to know out of the course materials and had clear expectations.

Total bird course. Only went to 2 classes, never opened the book, got an A+ (mind you it wasn't an easy A+, but if you went to class if would be). In the beginning it is a little boring (definition heavy) but gets more interesting at the end. No essay. Tests are watching movie scenes/multiple choice/short answer/match terms/fill in blanks.
